<h1>Fruits!</h1>
<h2>Apples!</h2>
<img src= "https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ7dokC4YaehO5lkAsgWIJQlDqN36WhURIj54164HvJ8nalWqey">
<p>Less than 100 calories in a medium-sized apple. Apples are free of fat, sodium and cholesterol. That same medium-sized apple contains 4 grams of dietary fiber.</p>
<h2>Grapes!</h2>
<img src= "https://steptohealth.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Red-grapes.jpg" width="300" height="200">
<p>A serving of a cup and a half of grapes contains just 90 calories, no fat, and virtually no sodium.</p>
<h2>Pineapples!</h2>
<img src= "http://assets.nydailynews.com/polopoly_fs/1.1064656.1334894616!/img/httpImage/image.jpg_gen/derivatives/article_750/pineapplefacts20n-1-web.jpg" width="300" height="300">
<p>Pineapples are excellent for immune system support. They also support bone strength while also being beneficial for your eyes.</p>
